  "title": "Accountant",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a General Accountant to manage day-to-day accounting operations, financial reporting, and compliance activities. The role will also involve basic cryptocurrency transaction handling and reconciliation, working closely with internal teams to ensure accurate financial records. <br /><br />Key Responsibilities</p><p><ul><li>Maintain a full set of accounts including AP, AR, GL, and bank reconciliations</li></ul><ul><li>Prepare monthly financial statements, management reports, and variance analysis<br /></li><li>Handle invoicing, expense claims, accruals, and journal entries</li></ul><ul><li>Record and reconcile inter-company transactions</li></ul><ul><li>Assist with budgeting, cash flow monitoring, and forecasting<br />Support audits, tax filings, and statutory reporting</li></ul><ul><li>Record and reconcile  cryptocurrency transactions<br /></li><li>Ensure compliance with internal accounting policies and procedures<br /></li><li>Assist in improving accounting workflows and internal controls<br /></li><li>Maintain organized financial records for audit and management review</li></ul></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma / Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance, or related field</li><li>2–5 years of relevant accounting experience</li><li>Strong understanding of double-entry accounting principles</li><li>Basic knowledge with cryptocurrency transactions or reconciliations</li><li>Basic knowledge of stablecoins and crypto wallets</li><li>Proficient in Excel / Google Sheets and accounting software</li><li>Experience with multi-currency accounting is a plus</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
